  75. ‌    type key = Ord.t

  77. ‌    type 'a t =
  78.         Empty
  79.       | Node of {l:'a t; v:key; d:'a; r:'a t; h:int}

  81. ‌    let height = function
  82.         Empty -> 0
  83.       | Node {h} -> h

  85. ‌    let create l x d r =
  86.       let hl = height l and hr = height r in
  87.       Node{l; v=x; d; r; h=(if hl >= hr then hl + 1 else hr + 1)}

  89. ‌    let singleton x d = Node{l=Empty; v=x; d; r=Empty; h=1}

  91. ‌    let bal l x d r =
  92.       let hl = match l with Empty -> 0 | Node {h} -> h in
  93.       let hr = match r with Empty -> 0 | Node {h} -> h in
  94.       if hl > hr + 2 then begin
  95.         match l with
  96.           Empty -> invalid_arg "Map.bal"
  97.         | Node{l=ll; v=lv; d=ld; r=lr} ->
  98.             if height ll >= height lr then
  99.               create ll lv ld (create lr x d r)
  100.             else begin
  101.               match lr with
  102.                 Empty -> invalid_arg "Map.bal"
  103.               | Node{l=lrl; v=lrv; d=lrd; r=lrr}->
  104.                   create (create ll lv ld lrl) lrv lrd (create lrr x d r)
  105.             end
  106.       end else if hr > hl + 2 then begin
  107.         match r with
  108.           Empty -> invalid_arg "Map.bal"
  109.         | Node{l=rl; v=rv; d=rd; r=rr} ->
  110.             if height rr >= height rl then
  111.               create (create l x d rl) rv rd rr
  112.             else begin
  113.               match rl with
  114.                 Empty -> invalid_arg "Map.bal"
  115.               | Node{l=rll; v=rlv; d=rld; r=rlr} ->
  116.                   create (create l x d rll) rlv rld (create rlr rv rd rr)
  117.             end
  118.       end else
  119.         Node{l; v=x; d; r; h=(if hl >= hr then hl + 1 else hr + 1)}

  121. ‌    let empty = Empty

  123. ‌    let is_empty = function Empty -> true | _ -> false

  125. ‌    let rec add x data = function
  126.         Empty ->
  127.           Node{l=Empty; v=x; d=data; r=Empty; h=1}
  128.       | Node {l; v; d; r; h} as m ->
  129.           let c = Ord.compare x v in
  130.           if c = 0 then
  131.             if d == data then m else Node{l; v=x; d=data; r; h}
  132.           else if c < 0 then
  133.             let ll = add x data l in
  134.             if l == ll then m else bal ll v d r
  135.           else
  136.             let rr = add x data r in
  137.             if r == rr then m else bal l v d rr

  139. ‌    let rec find x = function
  140.         Empty ->
  141.           raise Not_found
  142.       | Node {l; v; d; r} ->
  143.           let c = Ord.compare x v in
  144.           if c = 0 then d
  145.           else find x (if c < 0 then l else r)

  147. ‌    let rec find_first_aux v0 d0 f = function
  148.         Empty ->
  149.           (v0, d0)
  150.       | Node {l; v; d; r} ->
  151.           if f v then
  152.             find_first_aux v d f l
  153.           else
  154.             find_first_aux v0 d0 f r

  156. ‌    let rec find_first f = function
  157.         Empty ->
  158.           raise Not_found
  159.       | Node {l; v; d; r} ->
  160.           if f v then
  161.             find_first_aux v d f l
  162.           else
  163.             find_first f r

  165. ‌    let rec find_first_opt_aux v0 d0 f = function
  166.         Empty ->
  167.           Some (v0, d0)
  168.       | Node {l; v; d; r} ->
  169.           if f v then
  170.             find_first_opt_aux v d f l
  171.           else
  172.             find_first_opt_aux v0 d0 f r

  174. ‌    let rec find_first_opt f = function
  175.         Empty ->
  176.           None
  177.       | Node {l; v; d; r} ->
  178.           if f v then
  179.             find_first_opt_aux v d f l
  180.           else
  181.             find_first_opt f r

  183. ‌    let rec find_last_aux v0 d0 f = function
  184.         Empty ->
  185.           (v0, d0)
  186.       | Node {l; v; d; r} ->
  187.           if f v then
  188.             find_last_aux v d f r
  189.           else
  190.             find_last_aux v0 d0 f l

  192. ‌    let rec find_last f = function
  193.         Empty ->
  194.           raise Not_found
  195.       | Node {l; v; d; r} ->
  196.           if f v then
  197.             find_last_aux v d f r
  198.           else
  199.             find_last f l

  201. ‌    let rec find_last_opt_aux v0 d0 f = function

  203.           Some (v0, d0)
  204.       | Node {l; v; d; r} ->
  205.           if f v then
  206.             find_last_opt_aux v d f r
  207.           else
  208.             find_last_opt_aux v0 d0 f l

  210. ‌    let rec find_last_opt f = function
  211.         Empty ->
  212.           None
  213.       | Node {l; v; d; r} ->
  214.           if f v then
  215.             find_last_opt_aux v d f r
  216.           else
  217.             find_last_opt f l

  219. ‌    let rec find_opt x = function
  220.         Empty ->
  221.           None
  222.       | Node {l; v; d; r} ->
  223.           let c = Ord.compare x v in
  224.           if c = 0 then Some d
  225.           else find_opt x (if c < 0 then l else r)

  227. ‌    let rec mem x = function
  228.         Empty ->
  229.           false
  230.       | Node {l; v; r} ->
  231.           let c = Ord.compare x v in
  232.           c = 0 || mem x (if c < 0 then l else r)

  234. ‌    let rec min_binding = function
  235.         Empty -> raise Not_found
  236.       | Node {l=Empty; v; d} -> (v, d)
  237.       | Node {l} -> min_binding l

  239. ‌    let rec min_binding_opt = function
  240.         Empty -> None
  241.       | Node {l=Empty; v; d} -> Some (v, d)
  242.       | Node {l}-> min_binding_opt l

  244. ‌    let rec max_binding = function
  245.         Empty -> raise Not_found
  246.       | Node {v; d; r=Empty} -> (v, d)
  247.       | Node {r} -> max_binding r

  249. ‌    let rec max_binding_opt = function
  250.         Empty -> None
  251.       | Node {v; d; r=Empty} -> Some (v, d)
  252.       | Node {r} -> max_binding_opt r

  254. ‌    let rec remove_min_binding = function
  255.         Empty -> invalid_arg "Map.remove_min_elt"
  256.       | Node {l=Empty; r} -> r
  257.       | Node {l; v; d; r} -> bal (remove_min_binding l) v d r

  259. ‌    let merge t1 t2 =
  260.       match (t1, t2) with
  261.         (Empty, t) -> t
  262.       | (t, Empty) -> t
  263.       | (_, _) ->
  264.           let (x, d) = min_binding t2 in
  265.           bal t1 x d (remove_min_binding t2)

  267. ‌    let rec remove x = function
  268.         Empty ->
  269.           Empty
  270.       | (Node {l; v; d; r} as m) ->
  271.           let c = Ord.compare x v in
  272.           if c = 0 then merge l r
  273.           else if c < 0 then
  274.             let ll = remove x l in if l == ll then m else bal ll v d r
  275.           else
  276.             let rr = remove x r in if r == rr then m else bal l v d rr

  278. ‌    let rec update x f = function
  279.         Empty ->
  280.           begin match f None with
  281.           | None -> Empty
  282.           | Some data -> Node{l=Empty; v=x; d=data; r=Empty; h=1}
  283.           end
  284.       | Node {l; v; d; r; h} as m ->
  285.           let c = Ord.compare x v in
  286.           if c = 0 then begin
  287.             match f (Some d) with
  288.             | None -> merge l r
  289.             | Some data ->
  290.                 if d == data then m else Node{l; v=x; d=data; r; h}
  291.           end else if c < 0 then
  292.             let ll = update x f l in
  293.             if l == ll then m else bal ll v d r
  294.           else
  295.             let rr = update x f r in
  296.             if r == rr then m else bal l v d rr

  298. ‌    let add_to_list x data m =
  299.       let add = function None -> Some [data] | Some l -> Some (data :: l) in
  300.       update x add m

  302. ‌    let rec iter f = function
  303.         Empty -> ()
  304.       | Node {l; v; d; r} ->
  305.           iter f l; f v d; iter f r

  307. ‌    let rec map f = function
  308.         Empty ->
  309.           Empty
  310.       | Node {l; v; d; r; h} ->
  311.           let l' = map f l in
  312.           let d' = f d in
  313.           let r' = map f r in
  314.           Node{l=l'; v; d=d'; r=r'; h}

  316. ‌    let rec mapi f = function
  317.         Empty ->
  318.           Empty
  319.       | Node {l; v; d; r; h} ->
  320.           let l' = mapi f l in
  321.           let d' = f v d in
  322.           let r' = mapi f r in
  323.           Node{l=l'; v; d=d'; r=r'; h}

  325. ‌    let rec fold f m accu =
  326.       match m with
  327.         Empty -> accu
  328.       | Node {l; v; d; r} ->
  329.           fold f r (f v d (fold f l accu))

  331. ‌    let rec for_all p = function
  332.         Empty -> true
  333.       | Node {l; v; d; r} -> p v d && for_all p l && for_all p r

  335. ‌    let rec exists p = function
  336.         Empty -> false
  337.       | Node {l; v; d; r} -> p v d || exists p l || exists p r

  339.     (* Beware: those two functions assume that the added k is *strictly*
  340.        smaller (or bigger) than all the present keys in the tree; it
  341.        does not test for equality with the current min (or max) key.

  343.        Indeed, they are only used during the "join" operation which
  344.        respects this precondition.
  345.     *)

  347. ‌    let rec add_min_binding k x = function
  348.       | Empty -> singleton k x
  349.       | Node {l; v; d; r} ->
  350.         bal (add_min_binding k x l) v d r

  352. ‌    let rec add_max_binding k x = function
  353.       | Empty -> singleton k x
  354.       | Node {l; v; d; r} ->
  355.         bal l v d (add_max_binding k x r)

  357.     (* Same as create and bal, but no assumptions are made on the
  358.        relative heights of l and r. *)

  360. ‌    let rec join l v d r =
  361.       match (l, r) with
  362.         (Empty, _) -> add_min_binding v d r
  363.       | (_, Empty) -> add_max_binding v d l
  364.       | (Node{l=ll; v=lv; d=ld; r=lr; h=lh},
  365.          Node{l=rl; v=rv; d=rd; r=rr; h=rh}) ->
  366.           if lh > rh + 2 then bal ll lv ld (join lr v d r) else
  367.           if rh > lh + 2 then bal (join l v d rl) rv rd rr else
  368.           create l v d r

  370.     (* Merge two trees l and r into one.
  371.        All elements of l must precede the elements of r.
  372.        No assumption on the heights of l and r. *)

  374. ‌    let concat t1 t2 =
  375.       match (t1, t2) with
  376.         (Empty, t) -> t
  377.       | (t, Empty) -> t
  378.       | (_, _) ->
  379.           let (x, d) = min_binding t2 in
  380.           join t1 x d (remove_min_binding t2)

  382. ‌    let concat_or_join t1 v d t2 =
  383.       match d with
  384.       | Some d -> join t1 v d t2
  385.       | None -> concat t1 t2

  387. ‌    let rec split x = function
  388.         Empty ->
  389.           (Empty, None, Empty)
  390.       | Node {l; v; d; r} ->
  391.           let c = Ord.compare x v in
  392.           if c = 0 then (l, Some d, r)
  393.           else if c < 0 then
  394.             let (ll, pres, rl) = split x l in (ll, pres, join rl v d r)
  395.           else
  396.             let (lr, pres, rr) = split x r in (join l v d lr, pres, rr)

  398. ‌    let rec merge f s1 s2 =
  399.       match (s1, s2) with
  400.         (Empty, Empty) -> Empty
  401.       | (Node {l=l1; v=v1; d=d1; r=r1; h=h1}, _) when h1 >= height s2 ->
  402.           let (l2, d2, r2) = split v1 s2 in
  403.           concat_or_join (merge f l1 l2) v1 (f v1 (Some d1) d2) (merge f r1 r2)
  404.       | (_, Node {l=l2; v=v2; d=d2; r=r2}) ->
  405.           let (l1, d1, r1) = split v2 s1 in
  406.           concat_or_join (merge f l1 l2) v2 (f v2 d1 (Some d2)) (merge f r1 r2)
  407.       | _ ->
  408.           assert false

  410. ‌    let rec union f s1 s2 =
  411.       match (s1, s2) with
  412.       | (Empty, s) | (s, Empty) -> s
  413.       | (Node {l=l1; v=v1; d=d1; r=r1; h=h1},
  414.          Node {l=l2; v=v2; d=d2; r=r2; h=h2}) ->
  415.           if h1 >= h2 then
  416.             let (l2, d2, r2) = split v1 s2 in
  417.             let l = union f l1 l2 and r = union f r1 r2 in
  418.             match d2 with
  419.             | None -> join l v1 d1 r
  420.             | Some d2 -> concat_or_join l v1 (f v1 d1 d2) r
  421.           else
  422.             let (l1, d1, r1) = split v2 s1 in
  423.             let l = union f l1 l2 and r = union f r1 r2 in
  424.             match d1 with
  425.             | None -> join l v2 d2 r
  426.             | Some d1 -> concat_or_join l v2 (f v2 d1 d2) r

  428. ‌    let rec filter p = function
  429.         Empty -> Empty
  430.       | Node {l; v; d; r} as m ->
  431.           (* call [p] in the expected left-to-right order *)
  432.           let l' = filter p l in
  433.           let pvd = p v d in
  434.           let r' = filter p r in
  435.           if pvd then if l==l' && r==r' then m else join l' v d r'
  436.           else concat l' r'

  438. ‌    let rec filter_map f = function
  439.         Empty -> Empty
  440.       | Node {l; v; d; r} ->
  441.           (* call [f] in the expected left-to-right order *)
  442.           let l' = filter_map f l in
  443.           let fvd = f v d in
  444.           let r' = filter_map f r in
  445.           begin match fvd with
  446.             | Some d' -> join l' v d' r'
  447.             | None -> concat l' r'
  448.           end

  450.     let rec partition p = function
  451.         Empty -> (Empty, Empty)
  452.       | Node {l; v; d; r} ->
  453.           (* call [p] in the expected left-to-right order *)
  454.           let (lt, lf) = partition p l in
  455.           let pvd = p v d in
  456.           let (rt, rf) = partition p r in
  457.           if pvd
  458.           then (join lt v d rt, concat lf rf)
  459.           else (concat lt rt, join lf v d rf)

  461. ‌    type 'a enumeration = End | More of key * 'a * 'a t * 'a enumeration

  463. ‌    let rec cons_enum m e =
  464.       match m with
  465.         Empty -> e
  466.       | Node {l; v; d; r} -> cons_enum l (More(v, d, r, e))

  468. ‌    let compare cmp m1 m2 =
  469.       let rec compare_aux e1 e2 =
  470.           match (e1, e2) with
  471.           (End, End) -> 0
  472.         | (End, _)  -> -1
  473.         | (_, End) -> 1
  474.         | (More(v1, d1, r1, e1), More(v2, d2, r2, e2)) ->
  475.             let c = Ord.compare v1 v2 in
  476.             if c <> 0 then c else
  477.             let c = cmp d1 d2 in
  478.             if c <> 0 then c else
  479.             compare_aux (cons_enum r1 e1) (cons_enum r2 e2)
  480.       in compare_aux (cons_enum m1 End) (cons_enum m2 End)

  482. ‌    let equal cmp m1 m2 =
  483.       let rec equal_aux e1 e2 =
  484.           match (e1, e2) with
  485.           (End, End) -> true
  486.         | (End, _)  -> false
  487.         | (_, End) -> false
  488.         | (More(v1, d1, r1, e1), More(v2, d2, r2, e2)) ->
  489.             Ord.compare v1 v2 = 0 && cmp d1 d2 &&
  490.             equal_aux (cons_enum r1 e1) (cons_enum r2 e2)
  491.       in equal_aux (cons_enum m1 End) (cons_enum m2 End)

  493. ‌    let rec cardinal = function
  494.         Empty -> 0
  495.       | Node {l; r} -> cardinal l + 1 + cardinal r

  497. ‌    let rec bindings_aux accu = function
  498.         Empty -> accu
  499.       | Node {l; v; d; r} -> bindings_aux ((v, d) :: bindings_aux accu r) l

  501. ‌    let bindings s =
  502.       bindings_aux [] s

  504. ‌    let choose = min_binding

  506. ‌    let choose_opt = min_binding_opt

  508. ‌    let to_list = bindings
  509. ‌    let of_list bs = List.fold_left (fun m (k, v) -> add k v m) empty bs

  511.     let add_seq i m =
  512.       Seq.fold_left (fun m (k,v) -> add k v m) m i

  514.     let of_seq i = add_seq i empty

  516.     let rec seq_of_enum_ c () = match c with
  517.       | End -> Seq.Nil
  518.       | More (k,v,t,rest) -> Seq.Cons ((k,v), seq_of_enum_ (cons_enum t rest))

  520. ‌    let to_seq m =
  521.       seq_of_enum_ (cons_enum m End)

  523. ‌    let rec snoc_enum s e =
  524.       match s with
  525.         Empty -> e
  526.       | Node{l; v; d; r} -> snoc_enum r (More(v, d, l, e))

  528. ‌    let rec rev_seq_of_enum_ c () = match c with
  529.       | End -> Seq.Nil
  530.       | More (k,v,t,rest) ->
  531.           Seq.Cons ((k,v), rev_seq_of_enum_ (snoc_enum t rest))

  533. ‌    let to_rev_seq c =
  534.       rev_seq_of_enum_ (snoc_enum c End)

  536. ‌    let to_seq_from low m =
  537.       let rec aux low m c = match m with
  538.         | Empty -> c
  539.         | Node {l; v; d; r; _} ->
  540.             begin match Ord.compare v low with
  541.               | 0 -> More (v, d, r, c)
  542.               | n when n<0 -> aux low r c
  543.               | _ -> aux low l (More (v, d, r, c))
  544.             end
  545.       in
  546.       seq_of_enum_ (aux low m End)
  547. end
